# Pre-commit and Ruff (recommended before every commit)

Before committing or opening a PR, ensure **Ruff** (lint + format) passes. The preferred way is to use **pre-commit** so these run automatically on commit.

## Setup (one-time)

```bash
uv sync
uv run pre-commit install
```

Hooks are defined in `.pre-commit-config.yaml` and use the same Ruff config as CI (`pyproject.toml`).

## What runs on commit

- **Ruff check** with `--fix`: lint and auto-fix where safe (same as CI lint job).
- **Ruff format --check**: enforce formatting; if it fails, run `uv run ruff format .` and re-stage.

Manual run on all files:

```bash
uv run pre-commit run --all-files
```

## When suggesting or reviewing changes

- **Recommend** that contributors run `uv run pre-commit run --all-files` (or rely on installed hooks) before pushing so CI stays green.
- If CI fails on Ruff: suggest running `uv run ruff check .` and `uv run ruff format .` (or `uv run pre-commit run --all-files`) and fixing reported issues.
- Do not bypass or disable these checks in commits; keep pre-commit config and CI aligned (same Ruff version and config).

## Other lint (optional)

Markdown and other linters are documented in `docs/QUALITY_WORKFLOW_RECOMMENDATIONS.md`. Pre-commit currently enforces Ruff only; add more hooks there if the team wants them on commit.
